���銝����閮���怨�望�����閬�
Keywords: mechanical engineering
education, problem solving, creativity.
Hands-on
practice is very important in mechanical engineering education. In mechanical
engineering curriculum, there are four fundamental courses that emphasize
hand-on practice: workshop practice, engineering drawing, mechanical drawing,
and mechanical engineering experiments. However, in the mechanical engineering
departments of the universities in Taiwan, usually the teaching of
these courses is not effective, while the resource required by these courses is
very large. Currently, the goal of these courses is to practice techniques.
This goal is not suitable for mechanical engineering education in universities.
Enhancing
students��� creativity in mechanical engineering education has been widely
accepted by the mechanical engineering departments of universities. The ME
department of Yuan Ze university also emphasizes on ���creativity and hands-on
practice��� in teaching. As we are entering the 21st century, the
ability to create new things is necessary for the students to face the
challenge of the rapidly changing world. Creation has to be achieved through
hands-on practice. But here, ���hands-on practice��� does not mean practicing
techniques. Instead, it means the willingness and ability to solve a problem.
The purpose of this research project is to transform the aforementioned courses
from traditional ���technique-practicing��� courses into courses that emphasize on
enhancing students��� problem solving ability. These courses are expected to
encourage flexible thinking and creative problem solving methods. Through small
team projects, these courses are also expected to give students the experience
and ability to do team work.
